  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Newton fund, China</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Newton Fund Researcher Links Workshop grants provide financial support to bring together a UK and China bilateral cohort of Early Career Researchers to take part in workshops focusing on building links for future collaboration whilst enhancing their skills and experience of international engagement. This includes the development of ideas which may lead to further funding applications to the Newton Fund or other programmes.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The workshops are enabling Early Career Researchers to work together, building their capacity and encouraging them to collaborate with one another as well as with experienced researchers.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The workshops are supported by an important China in-country partner, National Natural Science Foundation of China, who offer matched funding to cover the workshop costs.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To support international development relevant research; to contribute to capacity building of early career researchers and to establish new researcher links or significantly develop existing links with the potential for longer term sustainability.</narrative>
  </description>
